The paper deals with the computational complexity of solving various problems related to tile-matching match-three games, which involves analyzing the game board and making strategic moves. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques to solve these problems, which could place it under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves game theory and analyzing the optimal strategies for playing these games, which could place it under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves geometric and combinatorial aspects of the game board, which could place it under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG).
